        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:3:2",
        "relations": null,
        "text": [
          " كَفَى بِالْمَرْءِ خِزْياً أَنْ يَلْبَسَ ثَوْباً يَشْهَرُهُ أَوْ يَرْكَبَ دَابَّةً تَشْهَرُهُ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya, form Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Abu Ismail Al Sarraj, from Ibn Muskan, from a man, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘It is sufficient disgrace for the man that he wears clothes by which he is defamed, or rides an animal which defames him’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Muhammad ibn ’Isma‘il from abu ’Isma‘il al-Sarraj from ibn Muskan from a man who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘It is enough humiliation for a man to wear a dress that causes public abhorrence or use such a stumper.’” "
          ]
        }
      },
